<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">The holotype was collected under a large stone near a stream, on a north slope at ca. 2700 m altitude.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Only known from type location in North Iran: Central Alborz Range (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Distribution of species from subgenus Platyderus Eremoderus in Iran and Afghanistan: Platyderus felixi sp. nov. (red circle), P. iranicus sp. nov. (blue circles), P. lassallei sp. nov. (yellow circles), P. davatchii (green triangle), P. ledouxi (red triangle), P. taghizadehi (blue triangle), P. klapperichi sp. nov. (black triangle), and P. afghanistanicus sp. nov. (red question mark)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.83840.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/695654" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Based on the habitus drawing and features noted in the original description (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3406/bsef.1969.21081" author="Morvan, P" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="192 - 198" refId="B40" refString="Morvan, P, 1970. Contribution a la connaissance des coleopteres carabiques de l'Iran. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 74 (1969): 192 - 198, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3406/bsef.1969.21081" title="Contribution a la connaissance des coleopteres carabiques de l'Iran." url="https://doi.org/10.3406/bsef.1969.21081" volume="74" year="1970">Morvan 1970</bibRefCitation>
: 194, fig. 6), 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. davatchii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davatchii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. davatchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is without doubt an 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeanne" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eremoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eremoderus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Eremoderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-species. For the time being, it is the westernmost and the least known representative of the &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morvan" authorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyderus davatchii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davatchii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Platyderus davatchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; species group. Study of the holotype or topotypical male specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. davatchii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davatchii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. davatchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a key issue that can help to decide whether its closest neighbor, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ledouxi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ledouxi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. ledouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is a separate species or its synonym. The distance between the population from Alamut Region (Qazvin County), referred to the former species, and the population south of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kelārdascht">Kelardascht</normalizedToken>
[= Hasankif; = Rudbarak] (Chalus County: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kelārdascht">Kelardascht</normalizedToken>
District), referred to the latter species is about 40-50 km in straight line.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
The record about 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. davatchii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="davatchii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. davatchii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from &quot;10 km S Hasan Keif&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="Lohaj, R" journalOrPublisher="Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="7 - 14" refId="B32" refString="Lohaj, R, Mlejnek, R, 2007. Two new species of Laemostenus (Antisphodrus) (Coleoptera: Carabiade) from Turkey and Syria. Acta Societatis Zoologicae Bohemicae 71: 7 - 14" title="Two new species of Laemostenus (Antisphodrus) (Coleoptera: Carabiade) from Turkey and Syria." volume="71" year="2007">Lohaj and Mlejnek 2007</bibRefCitation>
) actually concerns 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ledouxi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ledouxi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">P. ledouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
